cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.MS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with modal logic and its relationship with classical and intuitionistic propositional logic. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as modal logic is used in AI for reasoning about knowledge and belief. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as intuitionistic logic is used in programming language semantics. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as modal logic has been used in some machine learning applications. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the soundness and completeness of the logic w.r.t. a class of special Heyting algebras, which may involve mathematical software.
